## Why This Doesn't Break Under Pressure

1. **Each agent is stateless and cacheable** — if the dark pool API is down, you run on last known data with a staleness flag
2. **Orchestrator owns the rebuild decision** — prevents chart spam when markets are choppy and levels are moving 5 points every hour
3. **Conviction scoring is the filter** — the system ignores noise by design, only acts on multi-source confirmation
4. **State diffing prevents unnecessary redraws** — `should_rebuild()` compares old vs new state
5. **Each agent has its own cadence** — COT runs weekly, pivots daily, GEX every 5min — no single bottleneck
